---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Changelog"
  description="Application and Blues corpus release notes for GraphRoots."
  canonicalPath="/changelog"
>
  <article class="shell changelog-page reading">
    <p class="eyebrow">Release notes · 2026-07-22</p>
    <h1>Changelog</h1>
    <section id="application">
      <h2>Application 0.5.0</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Added a reproducible biography crawl and validated import pipeline for
          provisional artist connections.
        </li>
        <li>
          Expanded the exploratory graph from 117 to 1,181 pathways while
          keeping the 43 reviewed relationships unchanged.
        </li>
        <li>
          Preserved each provisional edge's specific explanation and direction
          rather than replacing it with generic graph copy.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="corpus">
      <h2>Blues corpus 0.7.1</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Added Ry Cooder and Rory Block with checked videos, profile sources,
          and revision-pinned biography citations.
        </li>
        <li>
          Added 15 provisional pathways, giving Cooder 10 graph relationships
          and Block 5.
        </li>
        <li>
          Rechecked Joe Bonamassa's 12 existing relationships and refined the
          provisional Eric Clapton influence classification.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="previous-release">
      <h2>Previous application release 0.4.3</h2>
      <p>
        Added the MIT License, About navigation item, and creator copyright in
        the global footer.
      </p>
    </section>
    <p>
      Repository details are maintained in <code>CHANGELOG.md</code> and <code
        >CORPUS_CHANGELOG.md</code
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .changelog-page {
    padding-block: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  section {
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  code {
    color: var(--color-gold);
    font-family: var(--font-meta);
  }
</style>
